Form:
1.Kisi bhi aplication kai liye main building block hota hai.
2.User se data lena and show krana yai form form se hi krate hai.



__________Angular mai two type forms hote hai___________

1.Template-driven forms
2.Model-driven forms (Reactive forms)

*********Template-driven forms:
Isme hum sara work template pr hi kr lete hai isliye isko Template-driven form bolte hai
but isme hum chote level pr work krte hai bade level pr is pr work krne pr problem aati hai.
isme unit testing krne mai bhot hi problem ho jati hai.

--------------------Template-driven forms Feature-------------------
1.Easy to use
2.Suitable for simple scenarios.
3.Similat to Angular 1.0
3.Isme bhi hum Two way data binding use krte hai.
4.Unit testing krne mai problem ho jati hai.


*********Model-driven forms (Reactive forms):
Isme hum component level pr work krte hai. and formGroup built in class ka use krke hum ek module create krte hai
uske bad module ko hum HTML form mai bind krdete hai.
iske liye hume ReactiveFormsModule ko app.module.ts file mai import krna pdta hai.

isko reactive form isliye bolte hai kyoki hum HTML mai bhot km work krte hai jb hum iss form ko use krte hai and isme 
daynamicaly work and testing bhot easy ho jati hai and yai codding sepret pasrt ho jata hai.





